<body>
    <header class="header">
        <h1>Moderate level</h1>
    </header>

    <main class="main-content">
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Maharashtra, Tamil nadu, Uttar pradesh, Madhya pradesh are some of the states that have implemented water conservation measures to address the issue</h2>
                <h3>Tips and technologies implemented in many states</h3>
                <div>
                    <h2>1. Drip Irrigation and Sprinkler Systems</h2>
                    <p>Drip Irrigation: Encourage farmers to use drip irrigation systems, which deliver water directly to the roots of plants, reducing wastage.</p>
                       <p> Sprinkler Systems: Use sprinkler systems for irrigating crops, which helps reduce water consumption compared to flood irrigation, especially in drought-prone regions.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://images.interestingengineering.com/images/import/2017/05/Drip-irrigation.jpg" alt="Drip Irrigation and Sprinkler Systems">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>2. Fix Leaks Immediately</h2>
                    <p>
                        Monitor for Leaks: Leaking taps, pipes, and toilets waste a significant amount of water. Regularly check your plumbing for leaks and repair them promptly to avoid unnecessary water wastage.Upgrade to Water-Efficient Fixtures: Install water-efficient faucets, showerheads, and toilets that use less water without compromising performance.
                    </p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                    <img src="https://www.anglianwater.co.uk/siteassets/household/services/how-we-fix-a-leak.png" alt="Fix Laks Immediately"></div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>3. Wasteshed Management </h2>
                    <p>Micro-Watershed Development: Develop small-scale watersheds to manage rainwater and prevent runoff. This can improve groundwater recharge and soil moisture retention, benefiting both agriculture and local water availability.
                        Check Dams and Nadi Revival: Construct and restore check dams, ponds, and small rivers (Nadis) to hold and conserve water, especially during the monsoon season.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://d77da31580fbc8944c00-52b01ccbcfe56047120eec75d9cb2cbd.ssl.cf6.rackcdn.com/e7650fa7-0212-4539-a0e7-5ffd79dd9dd8/watershed-management---teachoo.jpg" alt="Wasteshed Management">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>4. Sustainable Groundwater Management</h2>
                    <p>Rainwater Recharge Wells: Building recharge wells or percolation pits can help replenish the groundwater table.
                        Limit Groundwater Extraction: Encourage strict regulation of groundwater extraction, especially for agricultural purposes, to prevent over-exploitation of this resource.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://northkingsgsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/groundwater-levels_English.png" alt="Sustainable Groundwater Management">
                    </div>
                  </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
